OpenSSO - Server based Unit test.

Steps:
 1. Install Open Federation server
     - deploy the openfm.war and configure it
 2. Setup the test
     - unzip openfm/built/test/dist/openfm-server-test.zip to a directory
       in the same machine where openfm.war is deployed.
     - copy the AMConfig.properties and FederationConfig.properties that was
       generated in Step One to the test <directory>/classes directory
 3. Run the test
     - type "ant" to run all test suites; or to selectively run individually
       test suite, invoke the specific target in the ant build XML.
